Replace the /WHOALL command with /WHOALLLFG<br>
<br>
These are simple code changes that can solve a huge problem on this server.<br>
<br>
As soon as you go LFG your anon flag comes off and you are listed by class, zone, level just as on a normal server.<br>
<br>
Now this is the hard part-gonna take an additional 15 minutes for some programer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
As soon as you gain a group your LFG flag trips off (perhaps triggered by activation of the group window or something). This way you will come off the list and others who went LFG after you will move up the list.<br>
<br>
If you really want to go nuts, it can be sorted according to alignment, but not necessary. <br>
<br>
Am I wrong here? Is this too simple? Should we all get together and petition Verant for something like this? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A> at: 1/20/02 10:01:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 6:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> I've said this time and again, but what, precisely, is so hard about asking someone who's /LFG what his or her class and level is?  Takes two minutes, tops.<br>
<br>
This seems to be a &quot;solution&quot; to what is really a non-existant problem.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 1/20/02 6:57:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubroak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:08:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> Deleted <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubroak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broak</A> at: 1/20/02 7:22:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:25:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> I believe that's what friends are for.  Isn't that part of the point of this server?  To get to know people?<br>
<br>
I know who many of the mover-and-shaker Enchanters, Druids, etc are in my area.  I know who are clerics I deal and group with regularly.<br>
<br>
I've never had trouble with my /LFG flag on finding a workable group.  With a few well-placed /shouts, I typically get one or two /tells within minutes.<br>
<br>
And for places I know are going to be problems pulling a group together once I'm there, like Lesser Faydark, I'll get the group together in a city, like Kelethin, first.  Not only does this encourage social behavior, but it's also somewhat more realistic.<br>
<br>
Sorry, I just don't buy that this is as big a problem as some people want to make it out to be.  That's not been my experience, and there a ton of ways to &quot;work around&quot; it that are easy and well within the capabilities of any character.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, the argument doesn't hold water on its own merits.  If there are so few people in these zones that it's hard to find group-mates, then it shouldn't take long to send a /tell to each of the people in the zone asking them if they want to group and what their class/level is.  If, on the other hand, there are a lot of people in the zone, then finding a group really isn't a problem at all, as long as you put yourself out as looking for one.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:28:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> Well, here is the problem. If he is right next to you then it is fine. If you have an entire group of people of the right class, level, alliance standing right next to you each time you log, then you are right, the problem is non-existing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Problem is how often does that occure? How often are there enough people to work a doable group in 5 local zones?  How do you &quot;just ask&quot; on a limited population server that is further limited by alliance? <br>
<br>
See the problem is that you can't just shout across EC to know that there is a group around. You can't do a /who all cleric 10 15 to see if there is one around. No, you must run the entire zone asking each and every person their class, level and alliance. If you find noone in that zone, you must do the same in each zone.<br>
<br>
The way you ask your question, it sounds simple. I would have to ask what char and level you are that you think the problem is non-existant. My Barb Warrior knows that it is much. MUCH harder then that. It is a process that can take hours for a young warrior-especially with all the solo classes that people are choosing because of the group &quot;problem&quot;. <br>
<br>
  I can only imagine what its like for group dependant classes in the 30s and 40s. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:36:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;And for places I know are going to be problems pulling a group together once I'm there, like Lesser Faydark, I'll get the group together in a city, like Kelethin, first. Not only does this encourage social behavior, but it's also somewhat more realistic.&gt;&gt;<br>
