Again, I can only imagine...well, I don't have to, there are enough higher level players confirming it as a problem, the people I am reading about leaving are also confirming that it is a problem.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A> at: 1/20/02 8:02:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:43:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> There are many problems ..</span><hr size=1> .. with even basic LFG.<br>
<br>
1. Groups never ever scan for LFG players unless they have a specific need for a certain class.<br>
<br>
2. LFG people scan for groups all the time.  They have no way they can identify who needs a group, though.  They can't even check for groups in other zones -- you have to travel there and actually visit the spots.  This is like want to camp the SSOY on old-time blue's.  Run over, find out it's camped (or no players or all full groups).  Now you'll need to run someplace else.<br>
<br>
3. It is an incredible and monumental pain to send a tell to everyone in the zone asking level, class, and if they want to group or have a spot.  If they're fighting, they might miss it and if they get enough tells for groups, one more can be irritating.  That happened to me yesterday when I was grouped in Runnyeye -- made me want to throttle the poor innocent LFG'er.<br>
<br>
4. It breaks RP.  I personally find it breaks immersion to be constantly asked level/class when (if it worked) you could just look it up.  The only time you do a &quot;/&quot; or &quot;/ all&quot; is when you want to know.  So, if you think knowing that is bad for your RP, just don't use the command and find people by running about and /shouting.<br>
<br>
5. There is no zone-spanning messaging.  Both /shout and /auc have the same range as /yell.  Only /tell and /gu have longer reach.<br>
<br>
IMHO, I'd like almost all the extra rules removed.  However, for this one, I think it would work almost as well if the group leader had a &quot;/lfp &lt;message&gt;&quot; command so LFG people could find him and he could spend his time fighting (as he does anyway); eg.<br>
<br>
 /lfp 32-36 iceclad healer<br>
 /lfp 24-28 sol-a crowd (prefer bard)<br>
 /lfp old-seb rogue 201+ LP only<br>
 etc.<br>
<br>
Then LFG people could do &quot;/ all lfp&quot; and see all the groups that both need and want more players.  It doesn't break /roleplay, it lets groups xp, and it let's LFG folks hunt for groups -- all of which is what people do already, just with more effort.  This would work very nicely for all servers, too -- an important consideration when asking for features.  FV is way too small to have any special work peformed just for us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 7:46:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LFG-Has anyone thought of this sollution?</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;I believe that's what friends are for. Isn't that part of the point of this server? To get to know people?<br>
